WEBVTT

00:01.902 --> 00:03.871
Previously on The Riches.

00:03.937 --> 00:07.608
We're gonna have
ourselves a wedding.
Our boy and your girl.

00:07.675 --> 00:11.011
- [ Wayne ]
My daughter is a precious gem.
- Dale said it.

00:11.079 --> 00:13.013
Since when does Dale
make the rules?

00:13.081 --> 00:16.784
- I am the new boss.
He is the old boss.
- [ Bell Ringing ]

00:16.850 --> 00:18.086
Get over it.

00:21.222 --> 00:24.825
Life's a river, kid.
You gotta go where
it takes you.

00:24.892 --> 00:26.594
[ Mick ]
Where you goin'?

00:26.660 --> 00:29.130
Why don't you mind
your own business, Mick?
I want in on it.

00:29.197 --> 00:32.366
You want in on this?

00:32.433 --> 00:34.034
Come on!

00:34.102 --> 00:35.803
[ Wayne ]
You're in the wrong lane!

00:35.869 --> 00:36.870
Mick! Look out!

00:36.937 --> 00:38.639
[ Linda ]
Shit! Stop!

00:45.746 --> 00:48.116
I'm sorry.

00:49.583 --> 00:51.785
[ Dahlia ]
You wanna pretend
to be the dead guy?

00:51.852 --> 00:54.422
Wear his suits,
and me to be his dead wife?
[ Ginny ] I know everything.

00:54.488 --> 00:57.158
You don't know shit.
I know Wayne Malloy
stole the family bank.

00:57.225 --> 01:00.328
I know you are up to
your eyeballs in shit if you
don't get that money back.

01:00.394 --> 01:02.663
I know none of this is
helping your position here.

01:02.730 --> 01:05.399
My being here means you're
a dead man, Wayne Malloy.

01:05.466 --> 01:08.902
I think Dale would be mighty
interested in your address.

01:08.969 --> 01:12.573
What do you want,
Ginny Dannegan?

01:12.640 --> 01:14.542
Well, look who it is.

01:14.608 --> 01:17.378
- Hi, everybody.
- Who is that?

01:17.445 --> 01:19.980
- This would be Ken.
- Di Di's fiancÃ©.

01:20.047 --> 01:21.449
What?

01:21.515 --> 01:23.284
Why does he have to
stay with us?

01:23.351 --> 01:26.220
'Cause the fiancÃ©
stays with the in-laws
in the run-up to the wedding.

01:26.287 --> 01:27.755
It's tradition.
I'm not gonna marry him.

01:27.821 --> 01:30.358
[ Dahlia ]
Well, it's tradition.
That's all I'm saying.

01:30.424 --> 01:32.960
Holy shit.
I'd do anything
for you, Delilah.

01:33.026 --> 01:35.796
[ Dale ]
What kind of monster
steals the family bank?

01:35.863 --> 01:37.698
[ Dahlia ] He won't
do it again, on my honor.
It's over.

01:37.765 --> 01:39.900
Why don't you just
tell me where you are.

01:39.967 --> 01:41.302
You and the kids
can wait outside.

01:41.369 --> 01:44.905
Is that what
you think of me, Daddy? Can't
trust me to run the family?

01:44.972 --> 01:49.577
I-It's a real big burden,
being responsible
for a whole family.

01:49.643 --> 01:52.646
Don't feel bad at your daddy
for not picking you.

01:52.713 --> 01:57.084
[ Sobbing ]
All I ever wanted to do
was make you proud, Daddy.

01:57.151 --> 01:59.653
And I will carry you
in my heart...

01:59.720 --> 02:01.955
till the day that I die.

02:02.022 --> 02:04.225
[ Bell Ringing ]

02:08.796 --> 02:12.200
[ Buzzing ]

02:18.005 --> 02:20.140
[ Sighs ]

02:27.248 --> 02:29.350
[ Buzzing, Chirping ]

02:37.891 --> 02:39.760
[ Buzzing, Chirping ]

02:47.000 --> 02:50.771
[ Dahlia ] It's 4:30 in
the morning. What do you want?
[ Sobbing ]

02:52.873 --> 02:55.175
Dale? Is that you?

02:55.243 --> 02:58.011
Dale, what is it?

02:58.078 --> 03:01.915
He's dead.
My daddy's dead.

03:03.217 --> 03:05.386
Oh.

03:08.021 --> 03:10.658
Oh. What happened?

03:11.892 --> 03:14.262
He wanted to die.

03:14.328 --> 03:18.266
He crawled out
to the woods to die.

03:21.269 --> 03:23.404
Dale.

03:25.105 --> 03:26.974
The funeral's this weekend.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.812
You've gotta be there
for the family.

03:38.752 --> 03:40.588
I can't.

03:40.654 --> 03:43.357
You have to
be there for him.

03:43.424 --> 03:45.493
You gotta sing for him.

03:49.530 --> 03:52.433
Just bring back
the money, D.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.769
I'll take care
of things from here.

03:55.836 --> 03:57.738
I don't have it.

03:59.707 --> 04:01.609
Who are you, D?

04:02.810 --> 04:04.778
Are you one of us,

04:04.845 --> 04:07.315
or you one of them?

04:34.875 --> 04:37.110
[ Door Opens ]

04:37.177 --> 04:39.880
[ Door Closes ]

04:39.947 --> 04:41.882
Dahlia?

04:45.553 --> 04:48.356
[ Door Closes ]
Shit.

04:51.224 --> 04:53.361
[ Owl Hooting ]

04:58.399 --> 05:00.501
Have you reached
China yet?

05:01.669 --> 05:04.271
We've lost the money.
You're not gonna find it.

05:04.338 --> 05:06.474
He's dead.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.709
He loved us,
and we left him
like he was nothin'.

05:08.776 --> 05:11.712
How do you know?
Dale told me.

05:11.779 --> 05:15.649
Said Earl crawled off
in the woods to die.
He crawled?

05:15.716 --> 05:18.218
Look, would you
stop digging?

05:18.285 --> 05:20.521
Dale said if we just
pay back the money--

05:20.588 --> 05:23.391
Since when do you believe
a word Dale says?
Damn this.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.626
Look, I'm just gonna
go alone, Wayne.

05:25.693 --> 05:29.597
I'm gonna find the money,
I'm gonna take it back
and make things right again.

05:29.663 --> 05:32.366
You cannot make
things right again.

05:32.433 --> 05:34.668
So you don't want to go
pay your respects to Earl?

05:34.735 --> 05:36.470
This is a chance, Wayne,
to make amends.

05:36.537 --> 05:38.338
They don't want
our goddamn amends.

05:38.406 --> 05:40.273
How can you be so cold?

05:40.340 --> 05:43.176
He loved you.
And I loved him.

05:43.243 --> 05:47.314
- It's over.
- Oh, my God! I cannot
talk to you anymore.

05:47.381 --> 05:49.683
Maybe Dale lied.
Maybe Earl's not dead.

05:50.818 --> 05:52.986
He would never lie about
somethin' like that.

05:53.053 --> 05:55.689
You're so sure?
I choose to believe him.

05:55.756 --> 05:59.092
I choose to have faith
in the people I love.
You love Dale?

05:59.159 --> 06:02.430
Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.
Who do you want me
to love, Wayne?

06:02.496 --> 06:04.131
You want me to love
our neighbors?

06:04.197 --> 06:06.299
Your boss?

06:06.366 --> 06:10.103
All the lovely people who come
into my life, call me Cherien.
You want me to love them?

06:42.970 --> 06:45.839
We never use any
of this shit anyway.

06:45.906 --> 06:48.909
If you don't use it,
you really don't need it.

06:48.976 --> 06:50.578
What is she doing?

06:50.644 --> 06:53.046
[ Cael ]
She gonna hock all that?

06:53.113 --> 06:55.315
Mom, stop. We can't
hock the coffeemaker.

06:55.382 --> 06:58.519
Someone help me, please.

06:58.586 --> 07:01.088
Oh, you want
all this shit now,
don't you?

07:01.154 --> 07:04.492
See? That's what happens.
You start to believe that you
actually need it.

07:04.558 --> 07:08.195
- Baby, calm down.
- Know what?

07:08.261 --> 07:11.231
I'm not asking
for a single thing
from any one of you.

07:11.298 --> 07:13.501
I'm goin' by myself.

07:15.002 --> 07:17.838
Think she wants to
go to the funeral.

07:17.905 --> 07:20.007
You know how close
she was to Earl. And Susan.

07:20.073 --> 07:21.875
They were like her parents.
We can't let her go alone.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.777
Who knows what they're
gonna do to her there?

07:23.844 --> 07:27.047
If she goes,
we all go together.

07:27.114 --> 07:30.183
You can't go.
Why not?

07:32.820 --> 07:34.021
Shit.

07:34.087 --> 07:36.189
Yeah. Cael's right.
Your mother and I will go alone.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.826
[ Scoffs ]
You can't go either.
Dale wants to kill you.

07:38.892 --> 07:42.329
Dale wants $40,000.
Well, that's a lot
of silverware, Dad.

07:42.395 --> 07:46.066
- Yeah, well, I'll get it.
- You're gonna get
40 grand in cash?

07:47.334 --> 07:49.737
Okay. Count me in for three.

07:49.803 --> 07:52.540
- Brent still owes me.
- Who's Brent?

07:52.606 --> 07:54.407
Cael and Brent
are in business together.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.711
Yeah, I'll give him a call, have
the cash here tonight. Whoo!

07:57.778 --> 08:00.147
- What time is it?
- Oh, who knows?

08:00.213 --> 08:03.316
- Mom stopped all the clocks.
- Dahlia, put the bag down.

08:03.383 --> 08:06.219
You're not going anywhere.

08:10.924 --> 08:13.293
All right.

08:13.360 --> 08:16.964
If you go, we're all
going with you.

08:25.673 --> 08:28.208
Wow. Hey.
Which one's your office?

08:28.275 --> 08:31.879
Not telling you.
I want to know
where my dad works.

08:31.945 --> 08:33.914
That one.

08:33.981 --> 08:37.050
No shit. For real?
Don't steal anything.

08:37.117 --> 08:39.687
Come on.

08:39.753 --> 08:42.590
What do you mean,
"Don't steal anything"?

08:43.857 --> 08:45.859
[ Cael ]
What the hell is that?

08:46.794 --> 08:48.862
Barbecue at Hugh's.

08:50.998 --> 08:52.900
[ Clicks ]

09:01.074 --> 09:03.010
Goddamn small bills.

09:03.076 --> 09:06.146
Hey, isn't this what got us
in trouble in the first place?

09:06.213 --> 09:08.649
Get out of here.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.290
** [ Stereo: Country ]

09:19.627 --> 09:22.162
[ Knocking ]

09:24.965 --> 09:26.900
Cael?

09:29.202 --> 09:31.071
Cael, are you around?

09:33.874 --> 09:35.909
Come on, dude.
Where are you?

09:37.711 --> 09:40.648
** [ Country:
Man Singing, Indistinct ]

09:42.482 --> 09:46.053
Shit.
* Have faded away *

09:46.119 --> 09:48.021
[ Glass Shatters ]

10:00.567 --> 10:01.935
[ Sniffles ]

10:04.604 --> 10:07.975
Who are you?
Uh, Brent.

10:08.041 --> 10:10.110
Um, I was--
You want somethin'?

10:11.578 --> 10:14.081
Did you get a good look?

10:17.517 --> 10:20.854
You want to see me naked? Huh?

10:22.389 --> 10:24.424
Come in.

10:24.491 --> 10:26.559
Come on.
[ Sniffles ]

10:26.626 --> 10:28.662
** [ Continues ]

10:28.729 --> 10:31.098
[ Sniffles ]
Sit down.

10:35.535 --> 10:38.305
Let me tell you
somethin'.

10:38.371 --> 10:41.408
Women are smarter than you,

10:41.474 --> 10:43.977
and you gotta respect 'em.

10:44.044 --> 10:47.715
So when you're over there
in the door, peekin' in on me,

10:49.616 --> 10:52.319
you're takin' advantage
of my pain...

10:52.385 --> 10:54.321
for your own pleasure,

10:54.387 --> 10:56.323
and that's wrong.

10:56.389 --> 10:59.292
Look. I'm sorry.

10:59.359 --> 11:03.263
Okay, I didn't mean to
just stare at you.
What are you lookin' for?

11:05.565 --> 11:07.500
Love.
Love?

11:07.567 --> 11:11.772
Yeah.
Well, then you gotta
ask yourself a question.

11:13.373 --> 11:15.743
Who can I count on?

11:15.809 --> 11:17.911
How can I trust?

11:18.946 --> 11:21.014
'Cause if you can't
answer that,

11:22.983 --> 11:25.285
then you're gonna be
all alone.

11:31.391 --> 11:33.660
I thought--
Bobby.

11:33.727 --> 11:35.395
It's Brent.

11:35.462 --> 11:38.799
Lord, I appreciate
your sexual energy and all,

11:38.866 --> 11:41.769
but, you know, you're 17.

11:41.835 --> 11:46.539
You're Cael's friend.
I'm never, ever gonna
have sex with you.

11:46.606 --> 11:49.042
You understand that?

11:50.210 --> 11:52.112
Oh, honey.

11:52.179 --> 11:55.048
I mean,
don't get me wrong.
You're cute as a button.

11:56.784 --> 12:00.220
If I was gonna do
a 17-year-old, you'd
definitely have a shot.

12:01.755 --> 12:03.791
But...

12:03.857 --> 12:05.793
it's not meant to be.

12:05.859 --> 12:07.895
[ Whispers ]
Nope.

12:07.961 --> 12:10.730
** [ Continues, Faint ]
[ Sniffles ]

12:12.599 --> 12:14.701
Go on. Get out.
Get out.

12:14.768 --> 12:17.337
[ Chuckles ]
Go on.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.815
** [ Continues ]

12:31.218 --> 12:34.487
[ Man On Headphones ] Now,
this young alligator is between
three and five years old.

12:36.056 --> 12:38.892
[ Wayne ]
Ken, you know we're
going back for the funeral.

12:38.959 --> 12:42.395
Ken? You know we're
going back for the funeral.

12:42.462 --> 12:44.364
Ken?

12:44.431 --> 12:46.433
Ken!

12:46.499 --> 12:49.169
You know we're going back
for the funeral.
Yeah.

12:49.236 --> 12:51.371
Have you-- Have you seen
this alligator guy?

12:51.438 --> 12:53.273
Yeah. I know.
He's cool.

12:53.340 --> 12:55.475
I gotta talk to you.

12:55.542 --> 12:59.079
You know when there's
a Traveller funeral, there's
often a Traveller wedding.

12:59.146 --> 13:04.151
Now, your sister Ginny--
she may use this opportunity
to make you marry Di Di.

13:04.217 --> 13:07.020
Really? That's great.
No.

13:07.087 --> 13:09.156
Not great.
That's bad.

13:09.222 --> 13:11.624
You've got to
tell your sister no.

13:11.691 --> 13:13.726
Why?

13:13.793 --> 13:16.864
[ Sighs ]
She's too young.

13:19.232 --> 13:21.534
She's pretty, sure.
But she's too young.

13:21.601 --> 13:24.804
She's naive, she's gangly,
she doesn't know
what's what.

13:24.872 --> 13:27.774
You--
You're a man of the world.

13:27.841 --> 13:30.310
You've been around.
You've seen it.
You've seen a horse.

13:30.377 --> 13:34.014
You know,
you've played the field.
You've-- You've been in fields.

13:35.348 --> 13:37.350
Just you gotta
be strong here.

13:37.417 --> 13:40.320
You gotta protect her.
Well, I sure want to.

13:40.387 --> 13:42.923
I know you do.
So when your sister
Ginny says,

13:42.990 --> 13:44.892
"What about the marriage?"
you're gonna say--

13:44.958 --> 13:46.860
Yes.
N--

13:46.927 --> 13:49.029
No. It's a no sound.
N-N-No.

13:49.096 --> 13:51.131
No.
That's the one.

13:51.198 --> 13:54.567
Gotta say,
"I want to wait."

13:54.634 --> 13:56.269
I want to wait?

13:56.336 --> 13:59.606
I want to wait.
Much more positive.
I want to wait.

13:59.672 --> 14:02.809
I want to wait.
Now, that's more of
"I want to wait?"

14:02.876 --> 14:05.645
I want to wait.
Just go down.

14:05.712 --> 14:06.914
I want to wait.

14:06.980 --> 14:10.050
I want to wait.
Yeah.

14:13.486 --> 14:15.388
You're the man.

14:25.465 --> 14:30.203
[ Wayne ]
Dahlia! Let's go, baby!

14:30.270 --> 14:32.439
Come on!

14:32.505 --> 14:34.774
Shit.

14:34.841 --> 14:36.876
Ow.
Honey,

14:36.944 --> 14:39.346
if we want to get there,
we gotta get moving.

14:55.395 --> 14:58.265
[ Chattering ]

15:16.849 --> 15:19.286
Don't worry, guys.
Things get rough,
I'll protect ya.

15:19.352 --> 15:22.455
[ Scoffs ]
That brings us comfort, Ken.

15:22.522 --> 15:25.258
Don't laugh, honey.
We need his protection.

15:26.459 --> 15:29.029
Ken, try not to talk
about living with us, okay?

15:29.096 --> 15:32.665
Right.
Sure thing, Mr. Rich.

15:32.732 --> 15:35.435
Doug.
Let's go.

15:36.569 --> 15:39.672
How long we gonna stay?
We get in, we get out.

16:03.863 --> 16:06.166
[ Susan ]
Thank you for coming.

16:06.233 --> 16:09.069
Nice to see you too, Mick.

16:14.841 --> 16:16.776
Darlin'.

16:16.843 --> 16:18.178
Sorry.

16:23.216 --> 16:26.986
Oh, hello there, dear.
So glad you're here.

16:27.054 --> 16:30.057
Oh, I'm so glad
you're here for me.

16:30.123 --> 16:32.959
And you too, honey.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.162
Hi.
So glad you're here for me.

16:35.228 --> 16:37.330
I'm really sorry.

16:53.946 --> 16:56.015
I've gotta do this.
Dad.

16:57.984 --> 17:00.753
Stick with Di Di.
Don't waste your breath.
I'm comin' with ya.

17:04.791 --> 17:07.094
[ Chattering ]

17:08.061 --> 17:10.130
[ Woman ]
Yeah, I got it.

17:13.533 --> 17:15.435
I love what you've done
with the place.

17:15.502 --> 17:18.004
Look at you,
you son of a bitch.

17:18.071 --> 17:22.041
You're dressed like
the goddamn president
of the United States.

17:22.109 --> 17:24.277
How much that cost you?
Think I bought it?

17:24.344 --> 17:26.746
Such are the limits
of your imagination.

17:26.813 --> 17:29.249
[ Chuckles ]
Whatever.

17:30.583 --> 17:33.186
- Tell me where you're livin'.
- Do you want this or not?

17:33.253 --> 17:36.523
- How much you got?
- I want an oath of protection.

17:38.291 --> 17:41.161
Look, I'm sorry.

17:41.228 --> 17:43.696
But I'm gonna...

17:43.763 --> 17:46.766
tell you somethin'
right off the bat here,

17:46.833 --> 17:48.768
Mr. President.

17:48.835 --> 17:53.173
[ Chuckles ]
Whatever you got,
we want more.

17:54.874 --> 17:56.776
Haven't you heard?

17:57.944 --> 18:00.280
Everyone wants more.

18:06.153 --> 18:08.288
Get the other half
when we leave.

18:22.269 --> 18:26.173
Okay. I'll give you the oath.

18:30.577 --> 18:35.482
* My life flows on
in endless song *

18:35.548 --> 18:39.719
* Above earth's lamentation *

18:40.887 --> 18:46.125
* I hear the real
though far-off hymn *

18:46.193 --> 18:51.798
* That hails the new creation *

18:51.864 --> 18:57.370
* No storm can shake
my inmost calm *

18:57.437 --> 19:02.242
[ People Sobbing ]
* I hear the music singing *

19:03.843 --> 19:09.616
* It sounds an echo
in my soul *

19:10.883 --> 19:13.286
* How can I *

19:13.353 --> 19:17.624
* Keep *

19:19.259 --> 19:22.495
* From singin' **

19:24.264 --> 19:26.266
We love you.

19:26.333 --> 19:29.236
[ Man, Woman ]
Amen.

19:34.140 --> 19:36.243
[ Clears Throat ]

19:45.918 --> 19:48.788
It's good to have you back,
Wayne Malloy.

19:48.855 --> 19:50.790
Yeah.

19:53.360 --> 19:55.562
[ Dahlia ]
Thanks for this, Wayne.

19:55.628 --> 19:57.196
I love you.

19:57.264 --> 19:59.366
[ Woman Sobbing ]

20:01.368 --> 20:03.202
[ Dahlia ]
I gotta talk to Susan.

20:03.270 --> 20:06.072
Dahlia, we agreed.

20:06.138 --> 20:08.275
Let it go.

20:16.082 --> 20:19.452
- [ Di Di ] Don't even
think about it, Cael.
- I'm not an idiot.

20:19.519 --> 20:21.721
Congratulations, Di Di.

20:21.788 --> 20:25.091
- [ Di Di ] On what?
- Aren't you and Ken
gettin' married tonight?

20:25.157 --> 20:27.159
[ Chuckles ]

20:27.226 --> 20:29.228
Who told you that?

20:29.296 --> 20:31.698
Ginny. I think.

20:31.764 --> 20:33.566
Shit.

20:33.633 --> 20:35.568
She must have gotten to Ken.

20:35.635 --> 20:39.572
I got a really
bad feeling about
all this weddin' stuff, Dad.

20:39.639 --> 20:41.974
We gotta get
the hell out of here.

20:50.216 --> 20:52.184
Gave you 20 grand?

20:52.251 --> 20:54.321
Without missin'
a beat.

20:57.790 --> 21:01.461
And that night you saw
him, Cael was driving
a Mercedes, huh?

21:01.528 --> 21:03.996
Yellow, shiny and brand-new.

21:05.632 --> 21:09.268
Who the hell
does he think he is?
The king of Siam.

21:09.336 --> 21:13.072
- He betrayed us.
Every one of us.
- We ought to make him eat shit.

21:13.139 --> 21:15.508
SlÃ¡inte.
SlÃ¡inte.

21:18.311 --> 21:20.413
[ Exhales ]

21:20.480 --> 21:23.550
I heard you two were havin'
a rough couple of months.

21:23.616 --> 21:26.419
- I'm real sorry.
- Couple of years.

21:26.486 --> 21:29.155
- We manage.
- I'm tired of managin'.

21:29.221 --> 21:32.091
I would love to
help you guys out.

21:32.158 --> 21:34.761
- You deserve a piece
of the good life.
- You're damn right.

21:37.163 --> 21:39.231
Well,

21:39.298 --> 21:41.534
I got some money now.

21:41.601 --> 21:44.471
There's a lot of
insurance out on Daddy.

21:44.537 --> 21:46.706
I'd love to
pass some your way.

21:46.773 --> 21:49.776
Twenty-five g's sound like
a nice round number?

21:57.917 --> 22:01.654
Now, I'm not saying
get rid of Wayne,

22:02.922 --> 22:06.659
but if he disappeared,
que serÃ¡, serÃ¡.

22:09.896 --> 22:13.065
What exactly are you
sayin' here, Dale?

22:14.567 --> 22:16.903
[ Woman ]
He's gonna move up north
with his cousin.

22:16.969 --> 22:19.338
That's what he said last time
I talked to him.

22:26.479 --> 22:29.081
Hey, Ken. We gotta go.
Can't. I'm losin'.

22:29.148 --> 22:32.051
- It's solitaire, Ken.
- That's why it hurts so much.

22:32.118 --> 22:35.321
- Sam will play solitaire
with you in the R.V.
- Promise?

22:35.388 --> 22:37.624
Yeah.

22:37.690 --> 22:40.460
We're havin'
a wedding, Wayne.

22:40.527 --> 22:42.361
Somethin' dies,
something's born.

22:42.429 --> 22:44.931
Somethin' ends,
somethin' begins.

22:44.997 --> 22:48.234
- Dad.
- Okay, Ken.
We're leaving.

22:48.300 --> 22:51.738
Now's the time to say your
piece. Tell her what you really
think. Di Di's counting on you,

22:51.804 --> 22:54.441
and we want you
to be a man here.
I've been thinkin', Mr. Rich.

22:54.507 --> 22:58.411
You're your own man, Ken.
We're all counting on you
to do the right thing here.

22:58.478 --> 23:01.481
I'm trying to do
the right thing.
Well,

23:01.548 --> 23:04.150
now's the time
to say the N-O word.

23:14.794 --> 23:18.598
- No.
- Little bit
more ballsy there. "No."

23:20.166 --> 23:22.401
No. No. I-- I mean no.

23:22.469 --> 23:25.171
I'm sorry, Mr.--

23:25.237 --> 23:27.974
Doug. But I want to.

23:28.040 --> 23:31.678
I want to marry her.
I've always wanted to.

23:31.744 --> 23:34.481
I mean, ever since
before my fever.

23:35.482 --> 23:37.950
I mean,
I don't remember much,

23:38.017 --> 23:39.886
but I remember her.

23:40.887 --> 23:44.457
Ken, maybe--
No, it's okay, Delilah.

23:44.524 --> 23:46.626
'Cause I want to.

23:48.094 --> 23:50.497
And I'm gonna marry her.

23:50.563 --> 23:53.566
Well, the wedding's
happenin'.

23:53.633 --> 23:56.603
And it happens tonight,

23:56.669 --> 23:59.472
or I walk into that camp
and I start runnin' my mouth.

23:59.539 --> 24:03.042
You'll have about
a hundred R.V.'s parked outside
of Edenfalls by sundown.

24:14.020 --> 24:16.155
[ Dahlia ]
I thought he'd live forever.

24:23.362 --> 24:25.665
You shouldn't have left.

24:27.333 --> 24:29.201
You shouldn't have
taken that money.

24:30.903 --> 24:33.139
That's when
all the trouble came.

24:33.205 --> 24:36.175
Susan, I'm sorry
for what happened.
I am. I'm sorry.

24:36.242 --> 24:38.477
I hugged you in public.

24:38.545 --> 24:40.547
What more do you want?

24:40.613 --> 24:42.682
I just-- I--

24:42.749 --> 24:44.817
I miss you so much.

24:44.884 --> 24:48.087
I just-- I wanted to
talk to you like we used to.
Well,

24:48.154 --> 24:49.956
it's too late for all that.

25:03.002 --> 25:06.472
Why did Earl kill himself?
You go ask Dale about that.

25:06.539 --> 25:09.041
Why would I ask Dale?

25:09.108 --> 25:10.977
'Cause...

25:11.043 --> 25:13.279
maybe I don't want to
talk to you anymore.

25:16.115 --> 25:20.086
- How you feelin', Mama?
- I need a nap.

25:20.152 --> 25:22.254
Well, go take one.

25:38.104 --> 25:41.741
My daddy wanted us
to get married.

25:42.642 --> 25:44.844
Almost as much as I did.

25:44.911 --> 25:47.847
Almost as much as you did.

25:47.914 --> 25:50.850
Do you remember
that picnic...

25:50.917 --> 25:53.820
where you followed me
around all day long?

25:53.886 --> 25:56.122
Well,

25:56.188 --> 25:57.990
I was 14 years old.

25:58.057 --> 26:00.727
That first kiss.
You stole it.

26:00.793 --> 26:02.795
What's wrong with that?

26:08.534 --> 26:10.637
I love Wayne.

26:10.703 --> 26:14.340
What do you see in him?
I see myself.

26:16.876 --> 26:19.578
He asked you
to betray who you are.

26:29.989 --> 26:32.458
Tell me about Earl.
What about him?

26:32.524 --> 26:34.460
How'd he get down
to the woods?

26:34.526 --> 26:36.362
He crawled there.
I told you.

26:36.428 --> 26:39.131
He crawled there
on his hands and knees?
I reckon.

26:43.670 --> 26:45.938
Then what about the cuts?
What cuts?

26:47.039 --> 26:49.241
On his hands.

26:49.308 --> 26:51.577
Oh, yeah.

26:51.644 --> 26:53.846
Cuts on his hands
and his face.

26:53.913 --> 26:56.148
That must have been painful.

26:57.183 --> 26:59.285
What's with
all the questions, D?

26:59.351 --> 27:02.955
- I just want to know
what happened, Dale.
- I wasn't there, now, was I?

27:08.728 --> 27:10.863
Were you?

27:17.203 --> 27:20.740
What? You think
I carried him there?

27:22.174 --> 27:24.877
And just left him
there to die.

27:24.944 --> 27:26.979
Well, how'd he get
all them cuts then?

27:28.815 --> 27:30.883
Tryin' to crawl home?

27:34.586 --> 27:38.124
You really want to know
how he died?

27:43.529 --> 27:47.900
You really want to know
how he died.

27:49.836 --> 27:52.972
If he cried or--
or whimpered?

27:53.039 --> 27:55.141
Is that what
you want to hear?

28:07.854 --> 28:09.922
You left him there, D.

28:12.024 --> 28:14.761
You left him there
to suffer and die.

28:19.031 --> 28:21.067
Just as much
as anybody else.

28:27.173 --> 28:30.176
** [ Folk ]
[ Chattering ]

28:42.554 --> 28:46.092
Dahlia, we got a problem.

28:46.158 --> 28:48.027
What happened?

28:48.094 --> 28:50.963
You're shaking.
I'm cold.

28:51.030 --> 28:53.265
Baby, we've gotta leave.

28:53.332 --> 28:56.468
We gotta grab our little girl,
and we gotta run.
Dale killed Earl.

28:58.737 --> 29:01.941
How do you know?
Oh, he pretty much told me.

29:02.008 --> 29:04.110
[ Bell Clanging ]

29:05.244 --> 29:07.213
Y--

29:10.182 --> 29:11.951
[ Scoffs ]

29:12.018 --> 29:15.387
- God. Where the hell is Dad?
- I don't--
Look. Just play along, okay?

29:15.454 --> 29:17.656
Dad'll come up with somethin'.
He always does.

29:17.723 --> 29:21.427
- Yeah. It doesn't really
feel that way, Cael.
- Yeah, you--

29:21.493 --> 29:25.097
- Don't touch me.
You old bitch. God.
- Ow.

29:26.598 --> 29:29.601
[ Gun Cocks ]
Mick.

29:29.668 --> 29:32.104
Just who do you
think you are?

29:32.171 --> 29:34.740
That's what I want to know.

29:34.807 --> 29:39.846
'Cause I remember when you was
14 years old, and you was
just a scrawny little runt.

29:41.247 --> 29:43.482
Do you promise yourself
to Delilah Malloy...

29:43.549 --> 29:46.752
in body and in spirit,
in heart and in mind,

29:46.819 --> 29:49.255
forever and ever and always?

29:56.929 --> 30:00.099
Hi. Just wanted to talk.

30:00.166 --> 30:03.535
Do you want a drink?
No.

30:03.602 --> 30:06.873
You sure?
Yeah.

30:15.214 --> 30:16.715
You bet.

30:16.782 --> 30:21.921
And you, my child,
do you promise yourself
to Kenneth Dannegan...

30:21.988 --> 30:25.624
in body and spirit,
in heart and in mind?

30:25.691 --> 30:28.027
Mick, I see
where you're heading,

30:28.094 --> 30:30.329
but is there any chance
you could kill me later?

30:30.396 --> 30:33.665
They're trying to marry off
my little girl,
and I just gotta--

30:33.732 --> 30:36.268
Don't you move.
I can handle it.

30:36.335 --> 30:38.570
[ Linda ]
He's got a gun!

30:39.939 --> 30:42.174
Damn it, Dahlia.

30:42.241 --> 30:45.177
...forever and ever and always?

30:48.747 --> 30:53.352
Now you tell me why
you killed your daddy,
you brutal son of a bitch.

31:00.559 --> 31:03.029
No. I can't.

31:03.095 --> 31:06.598
I-- What the hell is wrong
with you people?

31:06.665 --> 31:08.600
Jesus!

31:11.137 --> 31:13.105
[ Crowd Murmuring ]

31:13.172 --> 31:15.307
[ Chuckles, Squeals ]

31:15.374 --> 31:18.077
Okay. Whoo!

31:19.478 --> 31:23.215
Yeah! You're bonded
together forever.

31:23.282 --> 31:25.251
Yeah.
Well, no. Not really.

31:25.317 --> 31:27.653
We'll handle it
from here, Father.

31:29.321 --> 31:31.257
Go on.

31:32.358 --> 31:36.062
[ Chuckles ]
What are you doin', D?

31:36.128 --> 31:38.797
Shut up.
Pack enough clothes
for a good long time.

31:38.864 --> 31:40.799
Go on.
[ Grumbles ]

31:40.866 --> 31:43.102
He was pushin' me out.

31:44.971 --> 31:47.739
Why did he hate me so much?
I loved him.

31:47.806 --> 31:50.376
I goddamn worshipped him.

31:50.442 --> 31:54.080
He was even choosin' that idiot
Ginny Dannegan over me.

31:54.146 --> 31:56.248
I mean, how much is a man
supposed to take, right?

31:56.315 --> 31:58.717
Zip it up.
You zip it up!

31:58.784 --> 32:00.652
[ Zipper Zips ]

32:01.954 --> 32:05.357
Now, you are gonna
write a letter.

32:05.424 --> 32:07.526
You're gonna tell
everyone what you did.

32:09.195 --> 32:12.264
And you're gonna explain to them
why it is you're leaving.

32:13.665 --> 32:15.701
I-- I don't wanna leave.

32:17.236 --> 32:19.371
I got nowhere to go.
Well, too bad.

32:19.438 --> 32:22.008
Now get a goddamn
piece of paper! Now!

32:26.145 --> 32:28.947
Just keep walkin'!
Don't talk to him.

32:29.015 --> 32:30.849
Where you live, Wayne?
Mick!

32:30.916 --> 32:34.120
- I want to know.
- I'm happy to tell you
whatever you want.

32:34.186 --> 32:36.422
[ Mick ]
I want to know
what you're doin'.

32:36.488 --> 32:39.325
I want to know what it's like.
I said don't talk to him!

32:39.391 --> 32:42.094
Aluminum siding.
Outside of Baton Rouge.

32:42.161 --> 32:44.330
- Aluminum sidin'?
- And it's heaven on earth.

32:44.396 --> 32:46.999
How dumb do you
think we are?

32:47.066 --> 32:49.468
Dumb enough to leave
the scene of an accident.

32:54.473 --> 32:57.309
[ Knocking ]
[ Ginny ] You let me in,
you little slut!

32:57.376 --> 33:00.246
God! Just leave me alone!

33:00.312 --> 33:03.015
- [ Knocking ]
- [ Glass Shatters ]

33:03.082 --> 33:05.184
You little whore.

33:05.251 --> 33:08.887
You ungrateful brat.
Do you have any idea what
I could do to your family?

33:08.954 --> 33:12.224
Why don't you just do it
already then, Ginny?
Because I can't take it anymore.

33:12.291 --> 33:14.893
Oh, you want me
to tell everybody
where you been livin'?

33:14.960 --> 33:19.898
Huh? All about
that big, beautiful house
and them beautiful cars?

33:19.965 --> 33:24.070
And how about that boy?
You know, the one that's got
his hands in your pants?

33:24.136 --> 33:27.173
[ Scoffs ]
Go away.

33:27.239 --> 33:30.642
You're not thinkin',
Di Di.
What about the cops?

33:30.709 --> 33:33.745
Want me to tell 'em
where your mama's livin'?

33:35.614 --> 33:37.749
About how she's
breakin' her parole?

33:38.817 --> 33:40.919
Hmm?

33:40.986 --> 33:43.755
No.

33:46.192 --> 33:48.494
What happened?

33:53.165 --> 33:55.334
Mick killed them.

33:55.401 --> 33:59.271
My whole family saw it all.
We haven't told anyone-- yet.

34:01.907 --> 34:04.676
Now you listen to me.

34:04.743 --> 34:07.546
Ken's gonna come up here
in about two minutes,

34:07.613 --> 34:10.216
and you're gonna
open that door.

34:10.282 --> 34:14.253
Then you two are gonna
consummate that weddin'.

34:16.388 --> 34:18.490
Ken's dream
is gonna come true.

34:19.658 --> 34:22.161
After that, I don't
give a shit what you do.

34:22.228 --> 34:24.763
You just want me to screw him?
Well, fine.

34:24.830 --> 34:27.366
Why don't you just
send him in here right now?
I'll screw him.

34:27.433 --> 34:29.535
I'll screw him right here.

34:41.180 --> 34:43.282
[ Door Opens ]

34:44.950 --> 34:46.818
[ Door Closes ]

34:48.954 --> 34:51.690
Get a pen. Go on.

34:54.793 --> 34:56.795
Sit down.

34:56.862 --> 35:00.832
Now, you write, "Dear Mama."

35:04.903 --> 35:07.306
- You're gonna kill me,
aren't you?
- Write it!

35:08.340 --> 35:10.709
[ Pen Scribbling ]

35:15.046 --> 35:18.317
[ Knocks ]
[ Door Opens ]

35:20.386 --> 35:22.621
[ Door Closes ]

35:50.582 --> 35:52.618
I guess we're
supposed to...

35:54.386 --> 35:56.488
c-consummate now.

36:02.961 --> 36:04.863
I-- I'm a virgin.

36:10.035 --> 36:11.903
Can you show me what to do?

36:12.971 --> 36:14.906
No.

36:18.444 --> 36:20.412
So why don't you
put that gun down, Mick,

36:20.479 --> 36:23.315
and we can just sit down,
and we can talk about this.

36:23.382 --> 36:25.617
You know,
the thing is...

36:26.952 --> 36:29.755
I think
you want in on it.

36:29.821 --> 36:33.359
I think you want in
on my aluminum siding deal.

36:33.425 --> 36:36.528
- I've made more money
than Jesus.
- Shut him up!

36:36.595 --> 36:39.565
I can't stand to listen
to any more of his lies!
Linda!

36:39.631 --> 36:41.600
He doesn't give a shit
about us!

36:41.667 --> 36:44.069
I want that money, Mick.
Give me that.

36:44.135 --> 36:46.672
Let go of the gun.
[ Gunshot ]

36:48.173 --> 36:50.075
[ Man ]
You hear somethin'?
[ Gasps ]

36:50.141 --> 36:52.311
[ Gasps ]

36:54.045 --> 36:57.283
You shot me,
you asshole!

36:58.684 --> 37:01.320
Oh, God.
[ Linda Whimpers ]

37:01.387 --> 37:03.555
[ Linda Groans ]

37:03.622 --> 37:05.591
Oh, God.

37:07.158 --> 37:09.295
This feels like a dream.

37:11.463 --> 37:13.231
Will you kiss me?

37:13.299 --> 37:15.233
I don't want to, Ken.

37:15.301 --> 37:17.168
Well, don't you love me?

37:17.235 --> 37:19.405
No.

37:21.673 --> 37:23.542
You think...

37:23.609 --> 37:26.011
maybe someday
you'll love me?

37:28.514 --> 37:30.582
I barely know what love is,

37:33.419 --> 37:36.488
but I'm pretty sure
I'm never gonna love you.

37:45.597 --> 37:47.733
Well, why are you
marryin' me then?

37:50.035 --> 37:53.071
Your sister's
threatening me.

37:53.138 --> 37:57.343
She says that if I don't
marry you, she's gonna send
my mom back to prison.

37:59.177 --> 38:01.747
- No, she won't.
- Yes, she will.

38:08.987 --> 38:10.889
Listen to me.

38:12.358 --> 38:14.526
I'll never let
my sister blackmail you.

38:16.928 --> 38:18.797
You understand?

38:20.766 --> 38:23.034
If you don't
want to marry me--

38:24.603 --> 38:28.374
if you want to live
in Edenfalls,
away from here,

38:32.043 --> 38:33.945
I'll protect you.

38:36.348 --> 38:38.784
I promise.

38:48.694 --> 38:50.762
[ Gasps ]
[ Door Closes ]

38:51.930 --> 38:53.832
[ Gasping ]

38:57.969 --> 39:00.939
- My pen ain't got no ink.
- Well, get another one.

39:04.576 --> 39:06.812
He tortured me.

39:06.878 --> 39:08.680
He hated me.

39:08.747 --> 39:10.248
Shut up.
You know it's true.

39:10.315 --> 39:12.418
I did it for you.

39:12.484 --> 39:14.920
For you.
I swear.

39:14.986 --> 39:16.855
I swear I needed you.

39:20.959 --> 39:22.828
Get down on your knees.

39:30.235 --> 39:32.471
I love you, Dahlia.

39:34.873 --> 39:37.576
And I want to die
10 times over...

39:37.643 --> 39:40.111
just to see you again.

39:52.591 --> 39:54.493
[ Gunshots ]

39:58.630 --> 40:01.032
[ Man ]
Hey. What's goin' on over there?
Dahlia.

40:01.099 --> 40:03.168
I'm not done.

40:03.234 --> 40:05.737
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

40:25.323 --> 40:29.160
I am through
with this place.

40:30.696 --> 40:33.499
My mama's always on my back.

40:36.434 --> 40:39.037
My pen ain't got no ink.

40:42.741 --> 40:45.376
This place is so small.

40:45.443 --> 40:47.546
[ Chattering ]

40:53.852 --> 40:56.354
Why won't you listen?
I don't know what
you're talkin' about.

40:56.421 --> 40:58.289
I'm talkin' about
the truth, Susan.

40:58.356 --> 41:01.860
You shouldn't have taken
the money, Dahlia.
What do you-- What money?

41:01.927 --> 41:04.329
I'm talkin' about your son
being a murderer.

41:04.395 --> 41:08.900
My son... did nothin' wrong.

41:08.967 --> 41:12.971
And if you'd been here,
nothin' ever would've happened.

41:13.038 --> 41:17.543
You blamin' me for what
your son did to your husband?

41:17.609 --> 41:20.211
You get out of here!

41:25.350 --> 41:27.252
[ Door Closes ]

41:32.558 --> 41:34.960
[ Chattering ]

41:38.263 --> 41:41.499
She didn't
want to hear it.

41:41.567 --> 41:43.501
[ Sighs ]

41:43.569 --> 41:45.571
Let's go, baby.

41:45.637 --> 41:48.306
You can't make
things right here.

41:48.373 --> 41:50.508
Come on.

42:00.251 --> 42:03.421
You hurt Di Di
in any way,

42:03.488 --> 42:05.724
hurt her family,

42:07.292 --> 42:09.127
I ain't your brother
no more.

42:11.496 --> 42:13.732
I'll choke you
while you sleep.

42:15.433 --> 42:17.803
Honey, get your
sister's dress.

42:29.648 --> 42:31.750
[ Chattering ]

42:35.353 --> 42:37.255
[ Engine Starts ]

43:00.411 --> 43:02.347
[ Sniffles ]

43:02.413 --> 43:05.116
Hey, Dale.

43:05.183 --> 43:07.218
Some day, huh?

43:11.857 --> 43:14.192
Can I ask you somethin'?

43:15.627 --> 43:18.096
Can you make someone
love you?

43:21.700 --> 43:23.702
What did you say about me?

43:27.538 --> 43:29.574
Nothin'.

43:29.641 --> 43:31.943
No, I-- I--
I didn't mean to--

43:39.184 --> 43:40.819
[ Groans ]

43:43.722 --> 43:45.824
[ Groans, Coughs ]

43:48.727 --> 43:50.829
[ Whimpers ]

43:52.363 --> 43:54.232
Where do they live?
